{n}You seem to hear thunder rumble in the distance. The nymph turns to leave, but suddenly raises her eyes to you and speaks again:{/n} "Do you know why I couldn't immediately recognize the intrusion, when you and the foolish little robin bard broke into my dreams?
Because it wasn't the first time I dreamt of you, {name}."
{n}With these words, the nymph's silhouette dissolves into thin air.{/n}
